{
  "texts": [
    "During matching, we first matched the ordered list of unigrams and bigrams to the title-to-occupation list and disambiguated using the modifier-to-occupation list when necessary.",
    "Once we successfully matched a title in title-to-occupation, the matched occupation was assigned to the associated tweet, and the rest of the ordered list was not examined.",
    "In other words, we assigned an occupation at the first match of a title.",
    "If no title was matched at the end of the ordered list, we performed an extra step to match the same ordered list of unigrams and bigrams to the keywordto-occupation list, but instead of assigning an occupation at the first match, we obtained a unique occupation by casting a majority vote from the list of matched occupations to achieve higher accuracy of occupation extraction.",
    "https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/konradb/chatgpt-the-tweets/versions/172"
  ]
}